steps.instruction:
### Prep
1. Remove the skin from the tomatillos and rinse well; chop them (about 4 cups)
2. Chop garlic and bell pepper, 1/2 of the jalapeño 
3. Zest the limes
4. Squeeze the limes for the juice 
5. Cut the pork into bite size pieces 

### Cooking
1. Combine the cut up pork, cumin, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1/4 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 teaspoon of canola oil 
2. Preheat large stock pot on medium high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
3. Place pork into pot, cook for 2 to 3 minutes
4. Place the remaining 1 teaspoon of oil into the pot
5. Add the onions, tomatillos and the garlic
6. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes
7. Sit in the lime zest and juice
8. Cover and reduce heat to medium low
9. Simmer for 60 to 65 minutes or until pork is tender
10. Stir the jalapeño and cilantro
11. Cook for 4 to 5 more minutes or until the peppers are tender
12. Serve (preferably over rice)
